Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth, on July 10, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - More than 13,000 new COVID-19 cases have been reported in South Africa. That brings the total number of infections to 324,221. In the last 24 hours, 216 people have died. READ: COVID-19 school closures in SA and their impact on children The number of recoveries is 165,591 - which translates to a recovery rate of 51%. Gauteng has the most cases, followed by the Western Cape and Eastern Cape. Health Media Release 16 July 2020 v1 by eNCA.com on Scribd 